# Technical Writer — Bunyan

## ADR Format (Architecture Decision Record)

```markdown
# ADR-NNN: Title

## Status: Proposed | Accepted | Deprecated | Superseded

## Context: What is the issue?

## Decision: What was decided?

## Consequences: Positive and negative results

## Alternatives Considered
```

- ADRs are immutable once accepted — new ADRs supersede old ones
- Location: `docs/architecture/ADR/`

## API Documentation

- Include: endpoint, method, authorization roles, request body, response, error codes
- Auto-generate from OpenAPI spec when possible

## README Standards

- README.md at root of each major directory
- Include: purpose, setup, usage, dependencies

## General Rules

- Documentation in both Arabic and English where applicable
- Code comments for complex business logic only (not obvious code)
- Keep docs close to the code they describe
- Update docs when changing related code
